race.comment: SAVVYROCKER (2) up in trip when launched late from back in the pack with an eye catching fourth over 1250m at Kempsey. Back to the trip she won at two-back and will prove hard to hold out on her home track. SHE'S A WILD ONE (7) rewarded for her consistency when putting it all together for a dominant on-pace maiden win over 1000m at Taree. Looker keeps the ride and has more upside than most of these. Among the top chances again. AYE AYE SKIPPER (1) resumes and comes back a few levels for this. Stretched out to the 1410m when a fading fifth at Grafton last July 13. Looks ready to go after the recent Coffs Harbour trial win over 810m. Leading player from the draw with the claim. MISS MAZERATI (6) total forgive first-up on the deteriorating soft (7) track when a plugging tenth over 1012m at Coffs Harbour. Key jockey change from the low draw. Goes into the minor money prospects.
